Management.
Radio.
The flagship station for the Timberwolves Radio Network is 830 WCCO (AM). WCCO became the team's radio home in 2011. Before that, KFAN (AM) had been the Timberwolves' Twin Cities flagship station since the team's inception, except for a brief two-year hiatus to KLCI BOB 106.1 FM for the 2006–07 and 2007–08 seasons. Alan Horton has been the team's radio play-by-play announcer since the 2009–2010 season.
Television.
The Timberwolves' games are broadcast on Fox Sports North. The broadcasters are Dave Benz and Jim Petersen.

